  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed combinations; a screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development to identify candidate high-influence inputs, and its qualitative findings are summarised in the UQ narrative. All 13 credibility factors are assessed and required levels are met or exceeded. Decision: Accepted.",
